@repository_layout
root:
- CareerSeeker.sln: .NET 8 solution.
- README.md: concise orientation and safety invariants.
- nuget.config: clears package sources for offline, package-free build.
- docs/: spec, roadmap, privacy/support/autonomy placeholders, this .mf handoff.
- src/: production projects and ports.
- tests/: console harnesses; no xUnit dependency.
important_docs:
- docs/CareerSeeker-Spec.md: authoritative v0.9 product and architecture spec.
- docs/CareerSeeker-Integration-Windows-Roadmap.md: integration sequencing.
- docs/CareerSeeker-Spec-5_6-LLM-Gateway.md: gateway economics and routing addendum.
- docs/Privacy-Policy.md: OAuth verification placeholder.
- docs/Support.md: OAuth support placeholder.
- docs/Autonomy-Contract.md: user-facing autonomy language placeholder.

@module_map
src/Scout:
- purpose: ingest public ATS feeds, normalize jobs, canonicalize title/company/location, detect remote/compensation/injection signals, deduplicate.
- key_files: Ats.cs, Scout.cs, Providers.cs, Http.cs, Dedup.cs, Canon.cs, Internal.cs.
- live_harness: tests/ScoutLiveHarness.
src/Store:
- purpose: single source of truth, SQLite schema, in-memory test store, audit chain.
- key_files: Schema.cs, ISeekerStore.cs, InMemorySeekerStore.cs, SqliteSeekerStore.cs, Ingest.cs, Audit.cs.
- note: SqliteSeekerStore.cs is included with Microsoft.Data.Sqlite; InMemorySeekerStore remains the dependency-free test/dry-run store.
src/Scorer:
- purpose: deterministic fit and legitimacy scoring; scam floor and red flag multiplier.
- key_files: Components.cs, Scoring.cs, Scorer.cs.
src/Researcher:
- purpose: retrieve company docs, derive grounded dossiers and positive-only legitimacy signals.
- key_files: Researcher.cs, Grounding.cs, Dossier.cs, Signals.cs, GatewayDossierModel.cs.
src/Gateway:
- purpose: LLM routing, budgets, provider contracts, pinned Gate policy, fake and HTTP providers.
- key_files: Routing.cs, Stages.cs, Gateway.cs, Budget.cs, Accounting.cs, Contracts.cs, ProvidersHttp.cs.
src/Tailor:
- purpose: generate resume/cover/answers, decompose candidate claims, apply hook safety.
- key_files: Tailor.cs, Drafting.cs, Decomposer.cs, GatewayTailorModel.cs, Hook.cs, Policy.cs.
src/TailorHookBridge:
- purpose: bridge Researcher dossier hooks into Tailor without direct cyclic dependency.
- key_files: DossierHookProvider.cs.
src/Verifier:
- purpose: Fabrication Gate claim entailment and exact/semantic verification.
- key_files: FabricationGate.cs, Claims.cs, Matchers.cs.
src/Pipeline:
- purpose: application lifecycle state machine and orchestration ports.
- key_files: ApplicationPipeline.cs, Lifecycle.cs, States.cs, Ports.cs, ClaimMapping.cs.
src/Dispatcher:
- purpose: package verified applications, build MIME, create Gmail drafts, detect application channels, perform local OAuth token flow.
- key_files: Dispatch.cs, Dispatcher.cs, Mime.cs, Packaging.cs, Recipients.cs, Providers.cs, GoogleOAuth.cs.
src/Engine:
- purpose: cycle scheduler, counters, localhost dashboard.
- key_files: EngineCore.cs, Host.cs.

@architecture_blueprint_local_first_boundary
schematic:
  +----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  | USER WINDOWS MACHINE                                                             |
  |                                                                                  |
  |  +---------------------+      +----------------------+      +------------------+  |
  |  | Windows Service     | ---> | Engine/Pipeline      | ---> | Local Dashboard  |  |
  |  | future host         |      | cycle orchestration   |      | localhost:7777   |  |
  |  +---------------------+      +----------------------+      +------------------+  |
  |            |                              |                            |          |
  |            v                              v                            v          |
  |  +---------------------+      +----------------------+      +------------------+  |
  |  | SQLite store        |      | DPAPI vault          |      | Generated docs   |  |
  |  | seeker.db, WAL      |      | OAuth/API keys       |      | PDFs/dossiers    |  |
  |  | hash-chain events   |      | local user scope     |      | local paths      |  |
  |  +---------------------+      +----------------------+      +------------------+  |
  |            |                              |                                       |
  +------------|------------------------------|---------------------------------------+
               |                              |
               v                              v
  +--------------------------+      +---------------------------+
  | Public external APIs     |      | User-authorized services  |
  | ATS feeds, LLM providers |      | Gmail OAuth compose only  |
  | web search/fetch         |      | future calendar/inbox     |
  +--------------------------+      +---------------------------+

boundary_rules:
- Resume/profile/tokens/database never leave the Windows machine.
- LLM calls receive only the minimum task data needed; job descriptions remain untrusted data.
- Gmail drafts are created in the user's own Gmail account via OAuth.
- Future Android reads state through a blind E2E relay only.

@architecture_blueprint_pipeline
schematic:
  Live ATS boards
      |
      v
  Scout --> DiscoveredJob --> Store.Ingest --> companies/jobs
      |                         |
      |                         v
      |                    Scorer + semantic scores
      |                         |
      v                         v
  Researcher ------------> dossier/signals
      |                         |
      v                         v
  Tailor <----------- DossierHookBridge
      |
      v
  Decomposer --> TailoredClaims
      |
      v
  Verifier / Fabrication Gate
      | pass                         | fail
      v                              v
  VERIFIED -> READY              BLOCKED_FABRICATION
      |
      v
  Dispatcher -> MIME -> GmailDraftClient -> Gmail Draft

l1_state_path:
- DISCOVERED
- SCREENED
- EVALUATED
- TAILORED
- VERIFIED
- READY
- DRAFTED

safety_assertion:
- READY is reachable only from VERIFIED.
- DRAFTED is reachable only from READY.
- Therefore a Gmail draft cannot be created without passing the Fabrication Gate.

@architecture_blueprint_module_dependencies
schematic:
  Leaves:
    Verifier
    Scout
    Gateway

  Core:
    Store depends on Scout
    Scorer depends on Scout

  Orchestration:
    Pipeline depends on Store, Tailor, Verifier, Dispatcher contracts
    Engine depends on Pipeline, Store, Scorer

  Content:
    Researcher depends on Gateway
    Tailor depends on Gateway, Verifier claim types
    TailorHookBridge connects Researcher -> Tailor

  Delivery:
    Dispatcher depends on Pipeline contracts
    Gmail OAuth and REST draft client live in Dispatcher

dependency_principle:
- Ports isolate network/OS edges.
- Test harnesses use fakes.
- Live harnesses exercise real adapters one connector at a time.

@architecture_blueprint_data_and_secrets
schematic:
  +-------------------+        +-------------------+        +----------------------+
  | Profile/resume    | -----> | Source claims     | -----> | Fabrication Gate     |
  | local onboarding  |        | Store.claims      |        | no unsupported prose |
  +-------------------+        +-------------------+        +----------------------+

  +-------------------+        +-------------------+        +----------------------+
  | OAuth client JSON | -----> | Google OAuth flow | -----> | DPAPI token vault    |
  | ignored by Git    |        | loopback browser  |        | ignored local file   |
  +-------------------+        +-------------------+        +----------------------+

  +-------------------+        +-------------------+        +----------------------+
  | Events table      | -----> | prev_hash/hash    | -----> | tamper-evidence      |
  | actor/kind/entity |        | chain             |        | VerifyAuditAsync     |
  +-------------------+        +-------------------+        +----------------------+

secret_rules:
- client_secret*.json is ignored.
- token*.json is ignored.
- .appdata/ is ignored.
- Provider keys must not be committed.
- DPAPI token vault is local user profile scoped.

@store_schema_summary
tables:
- profile: canonical user profile JSON and version.
- claims: atomic source-of-truth profile claims; Gate oracle.
- companies: ATS handle, company metadata, dossier path.
- jobs: normalized discovered postings, comp, remote, injection signals, simhash.
- scores: fit, legitimacy, red_flag_mult, total.
- applications: lifecycle state, autonomy level, artifacts, channel.
- gates: human approval gates for apply/reply/calendar/lesson.
- threads: Gmail thread association for future correspondence.
- events: hash-chained audit log.
- lessons: opt-in campaign learning.
- stories: STAR+R story bank.
- config: local settings and rails.
pragmas:
- journal_mode=WAL
- foreign_keys=ON
- synchronous=NORMAL
- busy_timeout=5000

@safety_invariants
- Fabrication Gate invariant: no action state is reachable except through VERIFIED.
- Pinned Gate invariant: Stage.VerifierEntailment is StrongCloud, never downgraded, never throttled.
- Dispatcher invariant: L1 Gmail port has no Send method.
- Gmail scope invariant: L1 requests gmail.compose only.
- Compose-only label invariant: custom label management is disabled by default because it requires broader Gmail scope.
- Researcher invariant: facts are grounded-or-dropped; no ungrounded dossier fact survives.
- Hook invariant: hooks that resemble candidate claims are omitted.
- Scorer invariant: total = min(fit, legitimacy) * red_flag_multiplier.
- Legitimacy floor invariant: low legitimacy jobs may be shown but not acted on.
- Scout invariant: job description is untrusted data and may signal prompt injection but is never instruction context.
- Store invariant: events form a tamper-evident hash chain.
- Server invariant: no hosted pipeline; future server relay is blind and E2E encrypted.

